what is Nutra?

Nutra means Nutraceutical in CPA/Affiliate marketing.
It usually refers to products related to:
•	Health supplements 
•	Weight loss pills 
•	Skin care / beauty creams 
•	Hair growth products 
•	Muscle gain / testosterone boosters 
•	Joint pain relief 
•	Diabetes / blood pressure supplements 
•	Sexual health products 

Examples:
•	Keto pills 
•	Slimming tea 
•	Anti-aging cream 
•	Hair oil / hair growth serum 
•	Detox supplements 

In CPA marketing, Nutra offers are popular because payouts are high.
Example:
User buys a weight loss product → you earn $20–$100+ CPA commission.
Example flow:
Facebook Ads → Nutra Landing Page → COD / Purchase Form → Sale → Commission

Types of Nutra offers:
1.	COD (Cash on Delivery)
Customer submits name + phone → Call center confirms → delivery. 
Example:
AdCombo → Weight Loss Product → COD Form → $10–$30 per confirmed order

2.	Trial Offer / Credit Card Submit
Customer pays shipping or trial fee. 
Example:
MarketHealth → Skin Cream Trial → user pays $4.99 shipping → you earn commission

3.	Straight Sale / E-commerce style
Customer buys directly. 
Example:
NutriProfits → Supplement → Full payment → commission

Why Nutra is popular:
✅ High payout
✅ Easy to scale with ads
✅ Works in many countries
✅ Emotional buying niche (নির্দিষ্ট বিষয়ভিত্তিক মার্কেট)

Why Nutra is risky:
❌ Many fake or exaggerated claims
❌ Ad platforms like Facebook / Google can ban ads for misleading health claims
❌ Refund / chargeback issues

Example ad angle:
“Lose 5kg in 7 days” ❌ risky / often banned
“Supports healthy weight management” ✅ safer

Best networks for Nutra:
•	AdCombo 
•	MarketHealth 
•	NutriProfits 
•	AdPump 
•	MyLead 

So simply:
Nutra = health/beauty/supplement product offers in CPA marketing.

